514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.052cbda7-f7d5-4934-b859-a480ba5423e6.description=
Sleeps for "X" seconds.

Inputs\:
seconds - The number of seconds to sleep.

Responses\:
success - Slept for "X" seconds.
failure - was unable to sleep for some reason
514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.4ea81102-8b99-4d4d-926e-026c17fbd238.prompt=Enter user 514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.6ad26eb8-7a87-493a-b023-e7b41590a592.description=Create a VM from a VM template. Must specify either hostSystem, clusterName, or vmResourcePool as a target location for VMs. Input Parameters\: vmName - name of the VM that will be created with this flow templateName - name of the VM template to clone in vCenter osType - linux or windows host - vCenter host to execute against user - vCenter username password - vCenter password vmDatacenter - target Datacenter on the vCenter host for the VMs dataStore - target datastore on the vCenter host for the VMs hostSystem - target ESX host for the VMs clusterName - target cluster for the VMs vmResourcePool - target resource pool for the VMs Responses\: success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0 failure - otherwise Result Fields\: serviceXml - xml representation of the server created in vCenter 514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.7e5399f1-3f19-470a-a8f4-6c21a27761a1.description=
Counts from one number to another number.

Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at
to - The number to count to
incrementBy - The amount to increment by during each count.
reset - If set to true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.
514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.895b6155-df91-4fe6-8183-0feb3531a996.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null. 
Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.8dab9dd2-b0f7-4588-b018-5f4f4f1ca66d.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.
514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.description=
Provision a VM from a VM template. Must specify either hostSystem, clusterName, or vmResourcePool as a target location for VMs.

Input Parameters\:
 host -  vCenter host to execute against
 user - vCenter username
 password - vCenter password
 port - Port Number toconnect on
 protocol - Connection prtocol(http, https)
 datacenterName -  target Datacenter on the vCenter host for the VMs
 hostname - VM Name
 templateReference - clone template Name
 dataStore -  target datastore on the vCenter host for the VMs
 hostSystem - target ESX host for the VMs
 CPUs - Number of cpus to be set on the VMs
 Memory - Amount of Memory in MB to be set on VMs. Memory should be a multiple of 4.
 availableCPU - Available CPU in  vCenter
 availableMemory - Available Memory in MB in vCenter
 disksize - Size of the disk space needed on the VM in GB
 toEmail - Email Address of the recepient to receive a Email Notification 
 fromEmail - Email Address of the Sender
 smtpHost - SMTP Hostname/IP Address
 smtpPort - SMTP Port

Responses\:
 success - The operation completed successfully.
 failure - Something went wrong.

Returns
 vmId - VM Identifies of the created VM
 ipAddress - IP Address of the created VM
 macAddress - MAC Address of the created VM
514d1847-8973-406c-8554-6df58de8d4cb.e096ebb7-658a-4ecf-808c-06e8e12d5751.prompt=Enter password
